VTradition renewed
p3
sVnews
p4
VAnanya is organising an evening of Hindustani music on January 31, 6 p.m. The event, &#8220;Nirantara&#8221;, will be held at Khincha Auditorium, on the premises of Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan, Race Course Road, Bangalore.The evening will feature a tabla solo by the 15-year-old Mihir Kallianpur, who is a disciple of Ustad Shabbir Nisar. This will be followed by a tabla duet by Shabbir Nisar and Mihir Kallianpur.  Ustad Shabbir Nisar is the son of the legendary tabla artiste Nawaz Ustad Shaik Dawood.There will also be a sitar duet by  Ustad Shahid Parvez Khan and his young son Shakir Khan.They will be accompanied on the tabla by Ustad Shabbir Nisar and Mihir Kallianpur.Nirantara brings to you performances in the  guru-shishya parampara. The concert is open to all.For details call Ananya on 23440409.
